The paper deals with deep learning architectures for speech separation and enhancement, which falls under the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SD). The paper also uses automatic speech recognition (ASR) to evaluate the results, which falls under the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also involves training deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with multi-speaker separation, which falls under the sub-category of Sound and Music Computing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves clustering techniques, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
